The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for image classification tasks in neuroimaging, specifically for detecting basal ganglia hemorrhage on noncontrast head CT. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study also evaluates the efficacy of different deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs), which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the findings, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
